Tile.Types.description:
Describes different types of tiles. Used by the Tile constructor 'type' param.

    Tile.Types = {
        floor: {
           name: 'Floor',
           char: '.',
           color: '#333',
           bgColor: '#111',
           passable: true,
           blocksLos: false
        },
        // ...
    }

example:
// 'P' will be ignored and a floor tile will be placed at that position
var mapData = [
    '####',
    '#..#',
    '#.Z#',
    '####',
],
charToType = {
    'Z': 'zombie'
};

entityManager.loadTilesFromArrayString(mapData, charToType);

